#Day3-31r
**Tables** <table></table> - container
Table headings are deffined with th tag
table rows are defined with tr tag
table data are defind with td tag

**Border** attribute is used to create border for a table!
<table border = "2" cellpaddinig =20px; </table>
**cell padding** is used to create space around the content
cell spacing is used to create spaces around the cells
width and height attributes are used to maintain table height and width.
- Can use %, px, etc.
Width can work with % but Height cannot work with %.(bcoz height can increase but width is just the screen size).
**bgcolor** attribute is used to change the color of cell, row etc.
color attribute is used to change the text color.

shortcuts for tags in VS code
type a enter it will create anchor tag
type h1 enter it will create h1 tag
type p enter it will create p tag

type table> to create a table row inside table
type tr> to create table data tag inside table row

h1+p+a (emmets) creates <h1></h1>, <p></p>, <a href=""></a>

+ symbol used to create siblings for tags
> symbol used to create child tags in table

table>tr*3>td*3
This creates table with three rows and three columns

table>tr*3>td*3{content inside}

() - for grouping
{}- for content
[] - for attribute
^ add element to the parent

html>head>title^body>h1 - This makes the below output

<html>
<head>
    <title></title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1></h1>
</body>
</html>

also can be written as html>(head>title) + body>h1 - This one also makes the same output as above

Use alt for moving lines of code up or down!! by selecting the line of code or maintain type cursor at the end of the line!!


Ctrl + shift + alt + up/down to edit multiple tags or add same content for multiple tags


shift + alt + up/down

